@node "1" "What is it?"

@{b}That is it:@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
This is a Graphic User Interface for the Midifile Player GMPlay.
It gives you all needed funktion to a nice GUI, including a playlist with autoplay funktion.@{line}

@endnode

@node "2" "What does it do?"

@{jcenter}
@{b}Supported options:@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
- Volume@{line}
- Programmpriority@{line}
- Mixingfrequency@{line}
- Playbuffers@{line}
- Polyphony@{line}
@{line}
- Forcing XG-Mode@{line}
- Forcing Mono-Mode@{line}
- Tonefilter@{line}
- Drumfilter@{line}
- Midifile-Info@{line}
@{line}
- GMPlay Output@{line}
@{line}
@{jleft}
For each Option you have the possibility to aktivate, deactivat and to do no settings (NS).@{line}
If one option is not set, it isn't used in the commandoline, which is used to start the GMPlay. The default by GMPlay is used.@{line}
@{line}
For more information about the options use the documentation, which is included in the GMPlay programmarchive!@{line}
@{line}
Importand:@{line}
The GMOut-Option must be activated for an ouput from GMPlay directly!@{line}

@endnode

@node "3" "What is needed?"

@{jcenter}
@{b}Requirements:@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
@{line}
- Amiga@{line}
- AOS3.0 or higher@{line}
- Correct installed GMPlay@{line}
    (GMP-G is tested with version 1.3 and 1.3a of GMPlay)@{line}
- Midifiles (to listen)@{line}

@endnode

@node "4" "Installation!"

@{u}Installation:@{uu}@{line}
@{line}
Nothing special. Copy the complet directory to the place wherever you want to have it.@{line}
@{line}

@endnode

@node "5" "Menu!"

@{b}Menu:@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
@{line}
  Project/About@{line}
    Programmers info@{line}
@{line}
  Project/Load Midi@{line}
    Open a filerequetser for loading a Midifile@{line}
@{line}
  Project/Quit@{line}
    Quit the GMP-G. If a Midifile is playing, it stops!@{line}
    (Same function as the close button of the window)@{line}
@{line}
  Project/Quit&Play@{line}
    Quit the GMP-G. If a Midifile is in use, the playing continous!@{line}
@{line}
@{line}
  Config/Load GMPlay@{line}
    Load the GMPlay programm.@{line}
@{line}
  Config/Save@{line}
    Save the configuration@{line}
    (Saved options: Buttons, the default directory and the window-possition)@{line}
@{line}
  Configs/AutoSave@{line}
    When aktivated, the configs of GMP-G are automaticaly saved on quit.@{line}
@{line}
@{line}
  Control/Start@{line}
    Same function as the play button. It starts the playback.@{line}
@{line}
  Control/Stop@{line}
    Same function as the stop button. It stops the playback.@{line}
@{line}
  Control/PlayListMenu@{line}
    This enhance the window to show the playlist and options! (Same like PlayList button)!@{line}

@endnode

@node "6" "Special!"

@{jcenter}
@{b}Sepcials:@{ub}@{line}
@{jleft}
@{line}
You can close the GMP-G with the menu "Project/Guit&P". The song, which is currently in use, continious with playing. You can restart the GMP-G and stop the playing with the Stop button.@{line}
Attention:@{line}
Playlist is inactiv in this mode.@{line}
@{line}
Exist in the programm directory a Playlist called "DefaultPlayList", so it will be loaded automaticaly on programm start!@{line}

@endnode

@node "7" "Problems"
@{b}Problems:@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
1.@{line}
The 14bit.driver of the GMPlay V1.3a has problemes with old Versions of NewIcons. Install the newest version!@{line}
2.@{line}
If the program quits of an internal error (no error message), so delete the GMP-G.prefs-file and try again.@{line}
Errors in this file can result in a programm crash, so don't edit them by yourself!@{line}
3.@{line}
The Programm doesn't start when the screen-resolution is to small. HiRes-Screen or higher is required.@{line}

@endnode

